[[Image:Ministry of Economics - Main entrance 02.jpg|250px|thumb|Ministry of Economy of the Republic of Poland]]
'''Ministry of Economy of the Republic of Poland''' ({{lang-pl|Ministerstwo Gospodarki}}) was a [[Ministry (collective executive)|ministry]] dealing with economy of [[Republic of Poland]].
Created in 1997 from reforms and mergers of other ministries, it has gone through several name changes and has recently been downsized, with issues related to work being split to [[Ministry of Labour and Social Policy of the Republic of Poland|Ministry of Labour and Social Policy]] and regional issues split to [[Ministry of Regional Development of the Republic of Poland|Ministry of Regional Development]]. In 2007 the bureau of tourism was moved to [[Ministry of Sport of the Republic of Poland|Ministry of Sport]].
The last [[Ministry (collective executive)|minister]] was [[Janusz Piechociński]]. In late 2015 it was merged into the new [[Ministry of Development (Poland)|Ministry of Development]].
