{{Infobox book |name=The End of White Christian America |image = [[File:Theendofwhitechristianamerica.jpg|200px]] |author=[[Robert P. Jones]] |language=English |pages= |publisher=[[Simon & Schuster]] |published=2016 |country=United States |media_type=Print, Ebook, Audiobook |isbn=978-1-5011-2229-3 |isbn_note=(Hardcover) }}
'''''The End of White Christian America''''' is a 2016 American non-fiction book by [[Robert P. Jones]].<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2016/08/15/white-christian-america-is-dying/ The Washington Post]</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/roomfordebate/2016/08/09/what-is-with-those-crowds-at-trump-rallies/trump-crowds-see-the-passing-on-white-christian-america The New York Times]</ref><ref>[https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2016/07/the-eclipse-of-white-christian-america/490724/ The Atlantic]</ref><ref>[http://www.alternet.org/books/end-white-christian-america-and-trumps-desperate-promises-save-it Alternet.org]</ref>
==Overview== Author Robert P. Jones, CEO of the Public Religion Research Institute, looks at the political and cultural changes of an America that is no longer a majority white [[Christianity|Christian]] nation.
==References== {{reflist}}
==External links== *[http://www.simonandschuster.com/books/The-End-of-White-Christian-America/Robert-P-Jones/9781501122293 Simon and Schuster]
